hopobject.body: Could I borrow your phone, please? cheap viagra canada free shipping Am I missing something? There is a federal regulation that requires states to halt medicaid payments if the states uncover “credible allegations of fraud.” If the states do not follow the federal guidelines, the Feds have the right to cut off medicaid payments. Since the Feds pay about 70% of all medicaid payments and federal law trumps state law pursuant to the supremacy clause, is it not wise to follow federal guidelines? Do the proponents of making payments to the suspended providers want to risk losing ALL federal medicaid payments to the state for failure to accede to federal guidelines?
